&lt;p&gt;Specialty Doctor (6 Sessions per week)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;HMP Peterborough is a Category B remand prison for both males and females with a current population 868 male prisoners and 372 female prisoners. The mental health in reach team at HMP Peterborough aims to provide mental health services equivalent to those available in the community. The in-reach team run a service targeted at both primary and secondary care levels and works closely with general practice colleagues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At HMP Peterborough the specialty doctor will have a role in working closely with psychiatric nurses and psychology colleagues in reviewing prisoners with mental health needs at the secondary care level, under CPA, or non-CPA care. The post requires an ability to conduct independent psychiatric assessment to establish diagnosis, assess risk and formulate treatment plans under supervision of a forensic consultant psychiatrist. The post holder will be expected to engage in the development of the MHIRT and engage in MDT forums not limited to Medication Management and MDT Clinical reviews for patients in the healthcare unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr Fiona Thompson, Clinical Director&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;01223 219610 (PA direct line)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
